1
00:00:59,020 --> 00:01:04,970
=Flower Sea=

2
00:01:06,050 --> 00:01:08,640
=Episode 9=

3
00:01:08,660 --> 00:01:09,500
Actually...

4
00:01:14,800 --> 00:01:15,690
I'm Chen Jing'an.

5
00:01:18,330 --> 00:01:19,250
Do you hear that?

6
00:01:20,620 --> 00:01:21,460
Zhu Niannian,

7
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:24,140
today's not April Fools'.

8
00:01:25,300 --> 00:01:26,180
Don't laugh.

9
00:01:26,930 --> 00:01:28,350
I'm dead serious.

10
00:01:28,850 --> 00:01:30,350
I really am Chen Jing'an.

11
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:33,390
Did you lose a dare

12
00:01:34,180 --> 00:01:36,050
with Chen Jing'an?

13
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:41,430
Think carefully,

14
00:01:42,180 --> 00:01:43,680
do you think the current Chen Jing'an

15
00:01:43,850 --> 00:01:45,100
is the same as before?

16
00:01:45,890 --> 00:01:46,890
Remember Li Minqiu

17
00:01:47,220 --> 00:01:49,550
Li Minqiu hit her head
with a basketball?

18
00:01:49,890 --> 00:01:52,350
Could that ever happen to me?

19
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:54,940
We

20
00:01:55,140 --> 00:01:56,800
switched bodies.

21
00:02:01,850 --> 00:02:04,850
You made up quite an elaborate story.

22
00:02:08,220 --> 00:02:09,890
You're asking for my ultimate move, huh?

23
00:02:14,430 --> 00:02:16,790
In grade 8, after fighting with your mom

24
00:02:16,850 --> 00:02:18,140
you ran away from home,

25
00:02:18,140 --> 00:02:19,550
took her bike,

26
00:02:19,930 --> 00:02:22,300
broke your leg on the way, and ended up

27
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:23,140
in the hospital.

28
00:02:23,550 --> 00:02:25,390
When I visited you in the hospital,

29
00:02:25,390 --> 00:02:26,890
you were sobbing,

30
00:02:26,890 --> 00:02:28,850
saying your mom didn't understand you.

31
00:02:29,550 --> 00:02:31,250
You even cried, begging me

32
00:02:31,250 --> 00:02:33,100
not to tell anyone
how pathetic you looked.

33
00:02:34,140 --> 00:02:35,180
Would I expose that

34
00:02:35,180 --> 00:02:36,390
just to trick you?

35
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:37,640
I swore an oath!

36
00:02:37,890 --> 00:02:39,600
Wait, wait.

37
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:40,600
Wait, wait, wait.

38
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:41,550
Hold on.

39
00:02:42,390 --> 00:02:43,260
Let me process this.

40
00:02:44,140 --> 00:02:45,270
Give me a second.

41
00:02:47,140 --> 00:02:48,010
I need a moment.

42
00:03:00,890 --> 00:03:02,180
Finish it, then let me copy.

43
00:03:02,970 --> 00:03:04,100
I don't know how.

44
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:05,600
Go on.

45
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:06,600
Don't be afraid.

46
00:03:07,510 --> 00:03:09,360
You'll definitely beat him this time.

47
00:03:09,890 --> 00:03:11,700
What's going on with you and Zhu Niannian?

48
00:03:11,700 --> 00:03:13,350
You've been acting more like her.

49
00:03:13,780 --> 00:03:14,760
Look,

50
00:03:14,900 --> 00:03:15,760
just like her.

51
00:03:15,770 --> 00:03:16,660
Nature calls—come with?

52
00:03:18,470 --> 00:03:19,600
I just got here.

53
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:21,600
I thought you were Deng Shasha. My bad.

54
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:22,740
You won't tell on me, right?

55
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:25,680
You're acting just like

56
00:03:26,390 --> 00:03:27,430
Chen Jing'an now.

57
00:03:31,300 --> 00:03:32,950
You've seriously...

58
00:03:33,590 --> 00:03:35,010
turned from Chen Jing'an

59
00:03:36,050 --> 00:03:36,890
into Zhu Niannian?

60
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:40,930
Am I dreaming?

61
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:44,550
Does this hurt?

62
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:47,940
Yeah.

63
00:03:49,220 --> 00:03:50,220
So what's really going...

64
00:03:50,390 --> 00:03:51,230
Voice down.

65
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:54,140
Did you experience

66
00:03:54,140 --> 00:03:56,100
something supernatural?

67
00:03:56,390 --> 00:03:57,230
Nonsense.

68
00:03:58,650 --> 00:04:00,050
There must be

69
00:04:00,050 --> 00:04:01,640
some scientific explanation.

70
00:04:01,890 --> 00:04:03,800
We just haven't figured it out yet.

71
00:04:04,050 --> 00:04:05,800
I'm only telling you this.

72
00:04:06,220 --> 00:04:07,320
Just the three of us know.

73
00:04:07,890 --> 00:04:08,850
Don't tell anyone else.

74
00:04:09,640 --> 00:04:11,220
I'm telling you because we're close.

75
00:04:12,640 --> 00:04:14,140
Don't worry.

76
00:04:15,300 --> 00:04:16,890
I'd never betray my buddy.

77
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:19,800
That's my buddy.

78
00:04:27,890 --> 00:04:29,600
Good morning, everyone.

79
00:04:30,260 --> 00:04:32,300
In spring's embrace,

80
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:33,430
we rise with pride,

81
00:04:33,670 --> 00:04:34,850
celebrating

82
00:04:34,850 --> 00:04:37,100
the 60th anniversary of our school.

83
00:04:37,350 --> 00:04:39,390
Nancheng TV will film the event.

84
00:04:39,850 --> 00:04:42,100
To showcase our students' spirit,

85
00:04:42,470 --> 00:04:46,050
we're selecting hosts for the ceremony.

86
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:48,720
Interested students can sign up

87
00:04:48,850 --> 00:04:50,430
at the student council office

88
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:51,720
before Wednesday.

89
00:04:52,470 --> 00:04:53,890
The TV station is coming?

90
00:04:53,890 --> 00:04:55,300
We'll be on TV?

91
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:57,100
Yeah. If you host,

92
00:04:57,100 --> 00:04:58,890
your parents can see you at home.

93
00:04:59,390 --> 00:05:00,640
Hosting's not for me.

94
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:02,970
You need looks and eloquence.

95
00:05:03,140 --> 00:05:05,300
My bet's on Zhu Niannian this time.

96
00:05:05,430 --> 00:05:06,300
Her?

97
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:08,140
She's just pretty.

98
00:05:08,470 --> 00:05:09,350
In terms of eloquence,

99
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,930
wasn't Liu Xinyi in first place

100
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:12,600
in the last speech contest?

101
00:05:12,850 --> 00:05:13,690
Exactly.

102
00:05:15,550 --> 00:05:16,390
I think it'll be her.

103
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:18,050
Agreed.

104
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,140
Well, I just think

105
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:32,350
she's only good-looking.

106
00:05:40,220 --> 00:05:41,140
Stop sighing.

107
00:05:41,140 --> 00:05:43,600
You're one of the most admired teachers.

108
00:05:43,890 --> 00:05:45,800
Why not perform at the event?

109
00:05:46,390 --> 00:05:47,640
In front of students?

110
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:49,180
I'd be embarrassed.

111
00:05:50,300 --> 00:05:52,390
Plus, I teach history.

112
00:05:53,300 --> 00:05:54,800
I have no talents.

113
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:56,440
Unless

114
00:05:56,970 --> 00:05:58,350
I perform a recitation

115
00:05:58,470 --> 00:06:00,300
of "Records of the Grand Historian"?

116
00:06:00,970 --> 00:06:01,930
Don't laugh.

117
00:06:02,140 --> 00:06:03,470
Help me think of something.

118
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:07,100
How about

119
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:08,600
a Hanfu fashion show?

120
00:06:09,100 --> 00:06:10,100
A Hanfu show?

121
00:06:10,550 --> 00:06:11,850
That's even more awkward.

122
00:06:12,550 --> 00:06:14,140
Why?

123
00:06:14,300 --> 00:06:15,720
Just treat it like lecturing,

124
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:16,890
walk a bit, then step down.

125
00:06:18,550 --> 00:06:19,390
Excuse me.

126
00:06:20,140 --> 00:06:21,010
Niannian,

127
00:06:21,220 --> 00:06:22,350
you're here to see Ms. Shi?

128
00:06:23,140 --> 00:06:24,140
I called her here.

129
00:06:24,310 --> 00:06:25,180
Zhu Niannian,

130
00:06:25,180 --> 00:06:26,470
the anniversary is coming up.

131
00:06:26,470 --> 00:06:27,250
No problem with

132
00:06:27,250 --> 00:06:28,890
the Romeo and Juliet performance, right?

133
00:06:29,100 --> 00:06:29,940
Performance?

134
00:06:32,550 --> 00:06:34,550
(Why is there a performance?)

135
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:36,680
(Zhu Niannian never mentioned this.)

136
00:06:40,540 --> 00:06:41,430
Tian Ye already knows

137
00:06:41,430 --> 00:06:42,550
about us switching.

138
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,140
He promised not to tell.

139
00:06:44,140 --> 00:06:44,980
Don't worry.

140
00:06:47,140 --> 00:06:48,050
Also,

141
00:06:48,050 --> 00:06:49,540
I originally planned to perform

142
00:06:49,540 --> 00:06:50,550
a dance show with Tian Ye

143
00:06:50,550 --> 00:06:51,680
for the anniversary.

144
00:06:52,140 --> 00:06:53,680
But suddenly, Ms. Shi asked me

145
00:06:53,970 --> 00:06:55,350
to do a play instead.

146
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:56,930
I didn't know the details,

147
00:06:57,140 --> 00:06:58,140
so I didn't dare refuse.

148
00:06:58,640 --> 00:06:59,550
This play

149
00:06:59,550 --> 00:07:00,600
is not that important,

150
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:01,600
right?

151
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:02,600
No.

152
00:07:02,780 --> 00:07:03,640
Last semester,

153
00:07:03,640 --> 00:07:05,720
Ms. Shi asked me

154
00:07:05,890 --> 00:07:07,390
if I wanted to join the play,

155
00:07:07,390 --> 00:07:08,550
and I agreed.

156
00:07:09,430 --> 00:07:10,850
I'm not

157
00:07:10,850 --> 00:07:12,350
that into acting,

158
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:13,550
but

159
00:07:13,550 --> 00:07:15,550
I couldn't refuse her.

160
00:07:15,970 --> 00:07:16,850
Good.

161
00:07:17,140 --> 00:07:18,050
I thought it was like

162
00:07:18,050 --> 00:07:19,800
the speech contest last time.

163
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:21,100
If I messed up, I'd be done for.

164
00:07:22,470 --> 00:07:23,430
If that's the case,

165
00:07:23,430 --> 00:07:25,180
I'll just find a way to back out.

166
00:07:25,180 --> 00:07:26,050
But

167
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:27,890
I already promised Ms. Shi.

168
00:07:28,100 --> 00:07:30,100
Wouldn't backing out be rude?

169
00:07:30,850 --> 00:07:32,140
It's not that important anyway.

170
00:07:32,140 --> 00:07:33,140
If I don't do it,

171
00:07:33,140 --> 00:07:34,390
they'll just find someone else.

172
00:07:34,550 --> 00:07:35,550
No big deal.

173
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:36,600
Besides,

174
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:38,550
even though I'm pretending to be you,

175
00:07:39,050 --> 00:07:40,640
I can't follow every single thing

176
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:42,140
you originally planned to do.

177
00:07:43,550 --> 00:07:45,350
As long as it doesn't cause trouble,

178
00:07:45,550 --> 00:07:47,680
I think I have the right

179
00:07:47,890 --> 00:07:48,890
to choose what I do.

180
00:07:48,970 --> 00:07:49,850
The same goes for you.

181
00:07:50,220 --> 00:07:51,430
After all, we don't know

182
00:07:51,430 --> 00:07:52,800
when we'll switch back.

183
00:07:53,300 --> 00:07:54,180
What do you think?

184
00:07:54,180 --> 00:07:55,890
You're right.

185
00:07:56,470 --> 00:07:57,350
Actually,

186
00:07:57,350 --> 00:07:59,100
I was planning to use your identity

187
00:07:59,100 --> 00:08:01,140
to audition for the host competition.

188
00:08:02,300 --> 00:08:03,680
Everyone would freak out!

189
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:04,890
Chen Jing'an as a host?

190
00:08:31,140 --> 00:08:32,100
(Help!)

191
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:33,890
(Why am I even standing here?)

192
00:08:37,040 --> 00:08:37,970
(Nancheng No.2 High School)

193
00:08:42,550 --> 00:08:44,600
What's that over there?

194
00:08:44,970 --> 00:08:46,140
That's the east.

195
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:48,800
Juliet is the sun!

196
00:08:50,140 --> 00:08:51,140
Arise,

197
00:08:51,390 --> 00:08:52,470
fair sun,

198
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:55,050
and kill the envious moon.

199
00:08:55,930 --> 00:08:58,350
(Is this guy for real down there?)

200
00:09:04,930 --> 00:09:06,850
Romeo, oh Romeo,

201
00:09:07,550 --> 00:09:09,550
why must you be

202
00:09:09,930 --> 00:09:11,220
Romeo?

203
00:09:14,140 --> 00:09:15,420
He's not a foot,

204
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:17,510
he's not a hand,

205
00:09:18,970 --> 00:09:22,100
he's not... a nose or face.

206
00:09:22,430 --> 00:09:23,390
What is he?

207
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,300
Juliet, you flubbed your line.

208
00:09:26,390 --> 00:09:27,350
I forgot.

209
00:09:27,350 --> 00:09:28,350
Quick, go on.

210
00:09:35,220 --> 00:09:36,720
Then I'll heed your words.

211
00:09:37,970 --> 00:09:39,720
Call me but love,

212
00:09:40,100 --> 00:09:42,050
and I'll be new baptized;

213
00:09:42,050 --> 00:09:43,470
Henceforth

214
00:09:44,050 --> 00:09:45,300
I never will be

215
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:48,100
Romeo!

216
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:54,550
What's the next line?

217
00:09:57,890 --> 00:09:59,180
Who are you?

218
00:10:01,970 --> 00:10:02,850
Are you

219
00:10:07,100 --> 00:10:08,140
from Inner Mongolia?

220
00:10:08,640 --> 00:10:10,300
Why are you standing here?

221
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:11,720
Romeo.

222
00:10:13,390 --> 00:10:14,230
Stop, stop.

223
00:10:15,640 --> 00:10:16,550
Zhu Niannian,

224
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:18,550
did you even memorize your lines?

225
00:10:18,890 --> 00:10:20,220
"Inner Mongolia"?

226
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:22,050
It's "Montague"!

227
00:10:30,890 --> 00:10:31,730
Ms. Shi,

228
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:34,390
this is too hard.

229
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:35,970
I just can't remember.

230
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:43,930
Zhu Niannian, what's wrong with you?

231
00:10:44,140 --> 00:10:45,140
Lines forgotten,

232
00:10:45,390 --> 00:10:46,600
props destroyed.

233
00:10:47,300 --> 00:10:48,140
Ms. Shi,

234
00:10:49,140 --> 00:10:50,720
I really can't memorize this.

235
00:10:51,890 --> 00:10:52,730
Niannian,

236
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:55,220
didn't Ms. Shi make you rehearse?

237
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:57,500
If you perform like this
at the anniversary,

238
00:10:57,500 --> 00:10:58,550
everyone will laugh at you.

239
00:10:59,350 --> 00:11:00,300
Ms. Yu...

240
00:11:00,300 --> 00:11:01,430
No more excuses.

241
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:02,640
Let's stop here today.

242
00:11:02,890 --> 00:11:04,220
Go home and study your lines.

243
00:11:04,550 --> 00:11:06,070
Next time, we'll do a full rehearsal.

244
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:08,600
Niannian,

245
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:10,300
you can do this. I believe in you.

246
00:11:10,470 --> 00:11:11,350
Go for it.

247
00:11:12,550 --> 00:11:13,390
Ms. Yu...

248
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:19,300
It's okay, Niannian.

249
00:11:19,550 --> 00:11:21,720
I thought you were amazing just now.

250
00:11:21,890 --> 00:11:22,890
I honestly felt like

251
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:25,390
the real Juliet was standing there.

252
00:11:28,350 --> 00:11:29,220
Um,

253
00:11:29,220 --> 00:11:30,350
Zhu Niannian,

254
00:11:30,550 --> 00:11:31,720
let me introduce myself.

255
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:33,890
I'm Wang Lihong from Class 1, Grade 10.

256
00:11:36,220 --> 00:11:38,600
Can I add you on QQ?

257
00:11:43,890 --> 00:11:44,730
What's wrong?

258
00:11:49,390 --> 00:11:50,260
Chen Jing'an,

259
00:11:50,430 --> 00:11:51,930
I heard Ms. Shi got mad

260
00:11:51,930 --> 00:11:53,220
during your play rehearsal.

261
00:11:54,180 --> 00:11:55,830
It's no big deal.

262
00:11:55,990 --> 00:11:57,510
I never wanted to act anyway,

263
00:11:57,510 --> 00:11:58,890
so I didn't memorize the lines.

264
00:11:59,550 --> 00:12:00,390
Chen Jing'an,

265
00:12:00,390 --> 00:12:01,800
maybe just do the play properly.

266
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:03,140
Don't antagonize Ms. Shi.

267
00:12:03,550 --> 00:12:05,550
Acting is easier than exams.

268
00:12:06,470 --> 00:12:07,430
Just treat it as

269
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:09,180
a relaxing after-school activity.

270
00:12:10,550 --> 00:12:12,300
What do you mean by "antagonize"?

271
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:13,930
You're the one who said

272
00:12:13,930 --> 00:12:15,300
you didn't want to do the play.

273
00:12:15,510 --> 00:12:16,350
What,

274
00:12:16,350 --> 00:12:18,180
you just blindly obey whatever she says?

275
00:12:18,470 --> 00:12:19,780
Don't you have your own thoughts?

276
00:12:20,430 --> 00:12:22,050
You're not a puppet.

277
00:12:22,430 --> 00:12:24,300
Where's your sense of self?

278
00:12:28,780 --> 00:12:29,790
I...

279
00:12:30,220 --> 00:12:32,140
I might've been too harsh, but...

280
00:12:32,140 --> 00:12:33,010
I get it now.

281
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:39,100
You're giving me attitude?

282
00:12:53,350 --> 00:12:54,190
What happened?

283
00:12:55,970 --> 00:12:57,220
Say something. What's wrong?

284
00:13:13,470 --> 00:13:14,350
Step down.

285
00:13:18,220 --> 00:13:19,430
Alright, class, settle down.

286
00:13:20,390 --> 00:13:22,550
We have a new classmate.

287
00:13:22,850 --> 00:13:24,640
Let's welcome him to introduce himself.

288
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:25,600
A round of applause.

289
00:13:32,890 --> 00:13:33,760
Hi everyone,

290
00:13:33,890 --> 00:13:34,890
I'm Li Minqiu.

291
00:13:35,100 --> 00:13:36,390
Call me "Mr. Li",

292
00:13:36,390 --> 00:13:37,730
